ining ones voice time, talking on the speakerphone to those one never has time for, or listening to recorded literature in a presence of ever-changing landscapes and events. Some use that time to think, rethink, reorganize, plan, or retrospect and find out some solutions. At the same time, we belong to the road with other cars, tracks, moving houses, other drivers, objects, and whatever we need to divide our attention for. The interior and the exterior intermix and become one unified world of a driver and a car.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We rely on the trucks for many reasons and it is part of our daily routine to pass a truck driver, or see a truck moving in front of us. The truckers spend a lot of time in their cars relying on technologies. They spend a lot of time behind the wheel and develop specific culture, routine, and habits. They share stories, and then feel some parts of them present in their heads during the long days or nights on the road. Everything has a deadline, expiration date, or a contract to obey.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In computing everything can be done many different ways with different approaches. This collaborative work suggests some solutions for particular moods displayed by selecting an area to hear some related to the area of an image tune, someones thoughts, and see them typed out for better comprehension.&nbsp;<br>We observe other drivers reacting to many signals prompting them to react properly. On the stop light we see all faces smiling of those turning left fast, as if theyd be immersed in a chair of a merry-go-round.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This work incorporates the topic of senses: what we lost as a kind (or a specie), how we support our senses, how we evoke different meaning by generating some interacting content, etc. We possess many more senses than our kindergarten teachers tell us about. We use them while driving, whether we acknowledge it, or not.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When the self-driving cars will fully take over, all that immersive experience of being part of the car will be replaced by the experience of a train, plane, a boat, or a taxi commuter. No concurrent attention, and not much interaction with the outside of the car world. New reality. Just one polite car.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Project Website<br></h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://www.cs.uml.edu/~stu/MM4.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"http://www.cs.uml.edu/~stu/MM4.html (opens in a new tab)\">http://www.cs.uml.edu/~stu/MM4.html</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Video Documentation</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/vimeo {\"url\":\"https://vimeo.com/303338872\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"vimeo\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://vimeo.com/303338872\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/vimeo -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Artist Bios</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Anna Ursyn runs Computer Graphics/Digital Media <g class=\"gr_ gr_5 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Grammar multiReplace\" id=\"5\" data-gr-id=\"5\">are</g> at the University of Northern Colorado. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Stuart Smith is a musician and a programmer with a career at the University of Massachusetts at Lowell</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Truckers\' Muse','','publish','closed','open','','truckers-muse','','\nhttps://vimeo.com/303338872','2018-12-07 16:23:58','2018-12-07 16:23:58','',0,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/?p=263',0,'post','',0),(264,1,'2018-12-05 06:02:14','2018-12-05 06:02:14','','Anna Ursyn and Stuart Smith 1','','inherit','closed','closed','','anna-ursyn-and-stuart-smith-1','','','2018-12-05 06:02:14','2018-12-05 06:02:14','',263,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Anna-Ursyn-and-Stuart-Smith-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(265,1,'2018-12-05 06:03:48','2018-12-05 06:03:48','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><a href=\"http://ursyn.com/\">Anna Ursyn</a> and <a href=\"http://www.cs.uml.edu/~stu/MM4.html\">Stuart Smith</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<p>[gallery ids=\"264\"]</p>\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Artist Statement</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our cars contain us. We are immersed in the commuting culture for most of our lives, no matter who does the driving. To many it is a me time, when driving alone, listening to the music, learning a foreign language, or memorizing a verse, singing along, training ones voice time, talking on the speakerphone to those one never has time for, or listening to recorded literature in a presence of ever-changing landscapes and events. Some use that time to think, rethink, reorganize, plan, or retrospect and find out some solutions. At the same time, we belong to the road with other cars, tracks, moving houses, other drivers, objects, and whatever we need to divide our attention for. The interior and the exterior intermix and become one unified world of a driver and a car.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We rely on the trucks for many reasons and it is part of our daily routine to pass a truck driver, or see a truck moving in front of us. The truckers spend a lot of time in their cars relying on technologies. They spend a lot of time behind the wheel and develop specific culture, routine, and habits. They share stories, and then feel some parts of them present in their heads during the long days or nights on the road. Everything has a deadline, expiration date, or a contract to obey.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In computing everything can be done many different ways with different approaches. This collaborative work suggests some solutions for particular moods displayed by selecting an area to hear some related to the area of an image tune, someones thoughts, and see them typed out for better comprehension.&nbsp;<br>We observe other drivers reacting to many signals prompting them to react properly. On the stop light we see all faces smiling of those turning left fast, as if theyd be immersed in a chair of a merry-go-round.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This work incorporates the topic of senses: what we lost as a kind (or a specie), how we support our senses, how we evoke different meaning by generating some interacting content, etc. We possess many more senses than our kindergarten teachers tell us about. We use them while driving, whether we acknowledge it, or not.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When the self-driving cars will fully take over, all that immersive experience of being part of the car will be replaced by the experience of a train, plane, a boat, or a taxi commuter. No concurrent attention, and not much interaction with the outside of the car world. New reality. Just one polite car.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Project Website<br></h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://www.cs.uml.edu/~stu/MM4.html\">http://www.cs.uml.edu/~stu/MM4.html</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Video Documentation</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/vimeo {\"url\":\"https://vimeo.com/303338872\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"vimeo\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://vimeo.com/303338872\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/vimeo -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Artist Bios</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Anna Ursyn runs Computer Graphics/Digital Media <g class=\"gr_ gr_5 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Grammar multiReplace\" id=\"5\" data-gr-id=\"5\">are</g> at the University of Northern Colorado. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Stuart Smith is a musician and a programmer with a career at the University of Massachusetts at Lowell</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Truckers\' Muse','','inherit','closed','closed','','263-revision-v1','','','2018-12-05 06:03:48','2018-12-05 06:03:48','',263,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/263-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(266,23,'2018-12-05 06:16:02','2018-12-05 06:16:02','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><a href=\"http://www.para-sight.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"George Themistokleous (opens in a new tab)\">George Themistokleous</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<p>[gallery ids=\"267,268,269,270,271,272\"]</p>\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Artist Statement</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In our hyper-connected age and the digital exteriorization of memory through computational extensions what happens to our physical bodies? As the physiology of the body is undergoes a digital transformation via 3d scanning, what does this mean for one\'s perception of their own body?<br>I attempt to explore these questions through a custom-made interactive media installation of my own making, the diplorasis. In the installation participants unexpectedly encounter three-dimensionalized projections of their selves in \'real\' time. How is the relationship between the actual self and its digital likeness defined through this encounter?&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Written Work</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":273,\"href\":\"https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/George-Themistokleous-Paper.pdf\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><a href=\"https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/George-Themistokleous-Paper.pdf\">George Themistokleous - Paper</a><a href=\"https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/George-Themistokleous-Paper.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button\" download>Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:file -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Project Website<br></h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.para-sight.org/installations-devices/4589953031\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.para-sight.org/installations-devices/4589953031</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Video Documentation</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/vimeo {\"url\":\"https://vimeo.com/304526724\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"vimeo\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://vimeo.com/304526724\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/vimeo -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Artist Bio</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>George Themistokleous is an architect and lecturer in architectural design, history <g class=\"gr_ gr_15 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Punctuation only-ins replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"15\" data-gr-id=\"15\">and</g> theory. He has studied architectural design, theory and art history at undergraduate (BA Hons. (dist), University of Toronto) and postgraduate levels (<g class=\"gr_ gr_11 gr-alert gr_spell gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim ContextualSpelling ins-del\" id=\"11\" data-gr-id=\"11\">MArch</g>, MA (dist), University of Brighton). The <g class=\"gr_ gr_12 gr-alert gr_spell gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim ContextualSpelling ins-del\" id=\"12\" data-gr-id=\"12\">inter-disciplinary</g> scope of his doctoral research operates between media, art <g class=\"gr_ gr_16 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Punctuation only-ins replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"16\" data-gr-id=\"16\">and</g> architecture. His practice focuses on the changing relationship between the visual body and space-time through emerging media that probe conventional limits between self and self-image, interior and exterior. The intertwined theoretical and design work is based on custom-made interactive multi-media installations. He is co-editor with T.Stoppani and G. Ponzo of the book This Thing Called Theory (Routledge).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Project Credits</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Project by: <strong>George Themistokleous</strong><br>Software Engineering: <strong>Savvas Socratous</strong><br>Hardware Engineering: <strong>Savvas Socratous, George Themistokleous</strong><br>Photographic/video documentation: <strong>George Athanasiou, George Themistokleous</strong><br>Electrical Engineer Consultant: <strong>Andreas Laoutas</strong><br>Actor in video documentation: <strong>Christophoros Liverdos</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Between the Self and the Digital Self-image','','publish','closed','open','','between-the-self-and-the-digital-self-image','','\nhttps://vimeo.com/304526724','2018-12-07 16:23:10','2018-12-07 16:23:10','',0,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/?p=266',0,'post','',0),(267,1,'2018-12-05 06:05:16','2018-12-05 06:05:16','','George Themistokleous 1','','inherit','closed','closed','','george-themistokleous-1','','','2018-12-05 06:05:16','2018-12-05 06:05:16','',266,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/George-Themistokleous-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(268,1,'2018-12-05 06:05:18','2018-12-05 06:05:18','','George Themistokleous 2','','inherit','closed','closed','','george-themistokleous-2','','','2018-12-05 06:05:18','2018-12-05 06:05:18','',266,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/George-Themistokleous-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(269,1,'2018-12-05 06:05:23','2018-12-05 06:05:23','','George Themistokleous 3','','inherit','closed','closed','','george-themistokleous-3','','','2018-12-05 06:05:23','2018-12-05 06:05:23','',266,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/George-Themistokleous-3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(270,1,'2018-12-05 06:05:29','2018-12-05 06:05:29','','George Themistokleous 4','','inherit','closed','closed','','george-themistokleous-4','','','2018-12-05 06:05:29','2018-12-05 06:05:29','',266,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/George-Themistokleous-4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(271,1,'2018-12-05 06:05:32','2018-12-05 06:05:32','','George Themistokleous 5','','inherit','closed','closed','','george-themistokleous-5','','','2018-12-05 06:05:32','2018-12-05 06:05:32','',266,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/George-Themistokleous-5.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(272,1,'2018-12-05 06:05:36','2018-12-05 06:05:36','','George Themistokleous 6','','inherit','closed','closed','','george-themistokleous-6','','','2018-12-05 06:05:36','2018-12-05 06:05:36','',266,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/George-Themistokleous-6.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(273,1,'2018-12-05 06:05:39','2018-12-05 06:05:39','','George Themistokleous - Paper','','inherit','closed','closed','','george-themistokleous-paper','','','2018-12-05 06:05:39','2018-12-05 06:05:39','',266,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/George-Themistokleous-Paper.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(274,24,'2018-12-05 06:13:39','2018-12-05 06:13:39','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><a href=\"https://www.sfbatchelor.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Stuart Batchelor (opens in a new tab)\">Stuart Batchelor</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<p>[gallery ids=\"275,276,277,278,279,280\"]</p>\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Artist Statement</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Between Worlds is a series of abstracts based on liminal space, both in the aesthetics of the pieces and the interdisciplinary approach taken in their creation. Working between the worlds of digital and physical media to create pieces both vivid and distant, between reality and virtual.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A memory of a real place, a shadow of the past, these liminal spaces of the mind are reflected in marks on the canvas - being neither wholly 2D shapes nor 3D forms, the viewer transitions from one to the other as they explore the works, mimicking the transient nature of life and their own experience.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The process involved in this work was itself between worlds - that of digital code and physical oil paint. Produced with C++ open source software openFrameworks, using data from scanned in paint, complex point clouds were generated to run simulations containing more than 1,000,000 particles. These were then used to paint, using both the artist\'s hand and the generative simulations to create the final images.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Project Website<br></h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.sfbatchelor.com/gallery\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"https://www.sfbatchelor.com/gallery (opens in a new tab)\">https://www.sfbatchelor.com/gallery</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Artist Bio</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We amputate ourselves when we create digitally. The sense of touch and spatial manipulation given from our hands and bodies have no connection to computers. By settling for computer interaction based on pictures behind glass, by technology bypassing the body and not being part of the physical environment, we slowly engender a future of immobility.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yet we have an entire body at our command, why would we not use it?&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I engineer systems that utilize the tactility of my hands as much as the logic of my mind, working between coding and painting in the same session, using technology to build a more immediate, improvised and natural environment. Escaping the paralysis of the screen to make a creative process based on intuition and feeling, assisted with technology.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These systems are the drive of my work; to develop a dynamic medium that we can see, feel and manipulate and to create works that draw on this wealth of untapped potential of human capability. Technology to bring us closer to reality, instead of propelling us away.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Between Worlds','','publish','closed','open','','between-worlds','','','2018-12-07 16:23:37','2018-12-07 16:23:37','',0,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/?p=274',0,'post','',0),(275,1,'2018-12-05 06:10:19','2018-12-05 06:10:19','','Stuart Batchelor 1','','inherit','closed','closed','','stuart-batchelor-1','','','2018-12-05 06:10:19','2018-12-05 06:10:19','',274,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Stuart-Batchelor-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(276,1,'2018-12-05 06:10:21','2018-12-05 06:10:21','','Stuart Batchelor 2','','inherit','closed','closed','','stuart-batchelor-2','','','2018-12-05 06:10:21','2018-12-05 06:10:21','',274,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Stuart-Batchelor-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(277,1,'2018-12-05 06:10:25','2018-12-05 06:10:25','','Stuart Batchelor 3','','inherit','closed','closed','','stuart-batchelor-3','','','2018-12-05 06:10:25','2018-12-05 06:10:25','',274,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Stuart-Batchelor-3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(278,1,'2018-12-05 06:10:33','2018-12-05 06:10:33','','Stuart Batchelor 4','','inherit','closed','closed','','stuart-batchelor-4','','','2018-12-05 06:10:33','2018-12-05 06:10:33','',274,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Stuart-Batchelor-4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(279,1,'2018-12-05 06:10:39','2018-12-05 06:10:39','','Stuart Batchelor 5','','inherit','closed','closed','','stuart-batchelor-5','','','2018-12-05 06:10:39','2018-12-05 06:10:39','',274,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Stuart-Batchelor-5.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(280,1,'2018-12-05 06:10:45','2018-12-05 06:10:45','','Stuart Batchelor 6','','inherit','closed','closed','','stuart-batchelor-6','','','2018-12-05 06:10:45','2018-12-05 06:10:45','',274,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Stuart-Batchelor-6.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(281,1,'2018-12-05 06:13:39','2018-12-05 06:13:39','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Stuart Batchelor</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<p>[gallery ids=\"275,276,277,278,279,280\"]</p>\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Artist Statement</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Between Worlds is a series of abstracts based on liminal space, both in the aesthetics of the pieces and the interdisciplinary approach taken in their creation. Working between the worlds of digital and physical media to create pieces both vivid and distant, between reality and virtual.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A memory of a real place, a shadow of the past, these liminal spaces of the mind are reflected in marks on the canvas - being neither wholly 2D shapes nor 3D forms, the viewer transitions from one to the other as they explore the works, mimicking the transient nature of life and their own experience.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The process involved in this work was itself between worlds - that of digital code and physical oil paint. Produced with C++ open source software openFrameworks, using data from scanned in paint, complex point clouds were generated to run simulations containing more than 1,000,000 particles. These were then used to paint, using both the artist\'s hand and the generative simulations to create the final images.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Project Website<br></h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.sfbatchelor.com/gallery\">https://www.sfbatchelor.com/gallery</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Artist Bio</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We amputate ourselves when we create digitally. The sense of touch and spatial manipulation given from our hands and bodies have no connection to computers. By settling for computer interaction based on pictures behind glass, by technology bypassing the body and not being part of the physical environment, we slowly engender a future of immobility.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yet we have an entire body at our command, why would we not use it?&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I engineer systems that utilize the tactility of my hands as much as the logic of my mind, working between coding and painting in the same session, using technology to build a more immediate, improvised and natural environment. Escaping the paralysis of the screen to make a creative process based on intuition and feeling, assisted with technology.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These systems are the drive of my work; to develop a dynamic medium that we can see, feel and manipulate and to create works that draw on this wealth of untapped potential of human capability. Technology to bring us closer to reality, instead of propelling us away.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Between Worlds','','inherit','closed','closed','','274-revision-v1','','','2018-12-05 06:13:39','2018-12-05 06:13:39','',274,'https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/274-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(282,1,'2018-12-05 06:16:02','2018-12-05 06:16:02','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><a href=\"http://www.para-sight.org/\">George Themistokleous</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<p>[gallery ids=\"267,268,269,270,271,272\"]</p>\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Artist Statement</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In our hyper-connected age and the digital exteriorization of memory through computational extensions what happens to our physical bodies? As the physiology of the body is undergoes a digital transformation via 3d scanning, what does this mean for one\'s perception of their own body?<br>I attempt to explore these questions through a custom-made interactive media installation of my own making, the diplorasis. In the installation participants unexpectedly encounter three-dimensionalized projections of their selves in \'real\' time. How is the relationship between the actual self and its digital likeness defined through this encounter?&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Written Work</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":273,\"href\":\"https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/George-Themistokleous-Paper.pdf\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><a href=\"https://urgency-reality.siggraph.org/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/George-Themistokleou